article.description: Chad Bowie had 22 points as Sam Houston State narrowly beat Louisiana Tech 71-68 on Sunday.
article.headline: Bowie lifts Sam Houston St. past Louisiana Tech 71-68
article.linkText: Bowie lifts Sam Houston St. past Louisiana Tech 71-68
article.story: HUNTSVILLE, Texas -- Chad Bowie had 22 points as Sam Houston State narrowly beat Louisiana Tech 71-68 on Sunday. Zach Nutall had 18 points for Sam Houston State (5-4), which earned its fourth consecutive home victory. Kai Mitchell added 15 points. Amorie Archibald had 20 points for the Bulldogs (6-3). Kalob Ledoux added 15 points and DaQuan Bracey scored 12. Sam Houston State plays Wiley at home next Sunday. Louisiana Tech matches up against Louisiana-Lafayette at home on Saturday. --- For more AP college basketball coverage: https://apnews.com/Collegebasketball and http://twitter.com/AP-Top25 --- Elements of this story were generated by Automated Insights, http://www.automatedinsights.com/ap, using data from STATS LLC, https://www.stats.com
